{"word":"συνᾴδω","slug":"συνᾴδω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνᾴδω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ᾴσομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to sing with</i> or <i>together</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>; <el>ς. ᾠδάν</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>to be in accord with</i>, <el>τινί</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to celebrate together</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}